paragraph.content:
for liquor, 1 L of spirits or table wine, or 4 L of beer or stout, and 1/2
                    L
                    of port, sherry or liqueur;

if grown, produced or manufactured in Hong Kong and not removed to a warehouse,
                before the goods are removed from the premises on which they were grown, produced or
                manufactured;

allow a reasonable time not exceeding 6 weeks, or such other period as the
                    Commissioner may allow after the duty becomes payable, for payment of the duty;
                    and

subparagraph.content:
the person in possession of it is not in possession, anywhere in Hong
                        Kong, of such alcoholic liquor of a total quantity exceeding 50
                        litres;

paragraph.content:
goods which the Commissioner shall, in his discretion, deem to be samples
                    or advertising matter and shown to his satisfaction to be of no commercial value
                    and not intended for re-sale;

goods which the Commissioner shall, in his discretion, consider to be bona
                    fide personal gifts sent to residents in Hong Kong and to be of no commercial
                    value and not intended for re-sale;

goods which are shown to the satisfaction of the Commissioner to have been
                    donated to bona fide charitable organizations for distribution within Hong Kong
                    without payment for the goods;

with the approval of the Commissioner in writing and subject to such
                    conditions as he may impose, diesel oil used in the blending of fuel oil in
                    licensed depots;

section.def:
factory
                (工廠) means any place or premises licensed for the
            manufacture of goods;

goods
                (貨品) means dutiable or duty-paid goods of the
            class or description for the manufacture of which a factory is licensed;

paragraph.content:
in the distillery there shall be one or more stores (hereinafter called
                        spirit
                        stores) for the collection and storage of all dutiable liquor;

subparagraph.content:
Port shall be free from added colouring matter and preservatives other than
                    alcohol and shall contain not less than 15% of alcohol by volume at
                    20°C;

